            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42131",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=aballard",
                        "name": "aballard",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Ballard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok, after trying a couple things, that idea isn't quite right. The fully qualified name likely has characters that are not valid for an id value. In the decorator, that seems to be solvable by using {{getId()}} instead of {{getFullyQualifiedName()}}. \r\n\r\nThe form element is a little more involved. At the time the code I posted executes, {{getId()}} does not yet address the {{belongsTo}} path. I guess the change I suggested could be pushed off to {{render($view)}}, where {{getId()}} returns the correct value. I don't know what side effects that might introduce, though.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=aballard",
                        "name": "aballard",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Ballard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-08-27T11:24:28.000+0000",
